Here we start    

/home/rchansen/apue2
                   /rch2       - directory to original code
                     rchnotes    - my notes
                     Sourcefiles - taken from apue/Source filesh

First get the tarball  start in  www.apuebbook.com
choose the 1992 version rt click
near bottom is version for  RedHat 6.0   click on Here is
to get  apue.linux3.tar.Z   put it in  /home/rchansen/apue2
prepare a new directory  mkdir rch2
get original code in top directory  tar -xzvh apue.linux3.tar.Z -C rch2 

in the /home/rchansen/apue2/rch2  set up for git  
after git init     git config --global core.editor vim       set editor
                   git config --global color.ui false        colors off
                   git config --list                         show vals

add for f      rchn   /home/rchansen/apue2/rch2/rchnotes
directory of my work  ~/apue2/rch2/ccode

use Sourcefile to get pgms into ccode
in dir ~/apue2/rch2/ccode

to get a file  mm.nn  dir/file  with
   :0r ../apue/dir/file
   make changes as needed
   ctrl-z
   compile as needed   usual is   gcc mm.nn.c    to put into a.out
   use fg  and jobs  to make corrections
   good luck  - rch  Wed 26 Aug 2020 09:27:07 PM CDT
